"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:9.5\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">9.5</span> 標題：水果乾壓成的餅塊（blocks of pressed dried fruit）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： אָשִׁישׁ, אֲשִׁישָׁה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ’ashish, ’ashishah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:19\">2SA 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:3\">1CH 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:5\">SNG 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:7\">ISA 16:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1\">HOS 3:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： דְּבֵלָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： dvelah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:18\">1SA 25:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:41\">1CH 12:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： παλάθη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： palathē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:5\">JDT 10:5</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>以色列人將無花果曬乾，然後壓成塊狀，以便儲存和運輸。葡萄乾也是這樣處理。關於乾水果塊用作藥物，參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.15.2 無花果餅 (poultice, fig cake)&lt;REALIA:1.15.2&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>關於無花果樹和葡萄樹，分別參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.6 無花果 (fig)&lt;FLORA:2.6&gt;</a> 和<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.12 葡萄树 (vine)&lt;FLORA:2.12&gt;</a> 。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:18\">1SA 25:18</a> ，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"God&#x27;s Word Translation\">GW</abbr> 譯作“fig cakes”（「無花果糕」），但這種譯法可能會讓人誤以為是加了無花果烤成的糕點。我們參閱的大多數譯本也用了“cakes”（「糕、餅」）這個詞，但一般用在短語中，例如「無花果塊做的餅」（“cakes of pressed figs”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> ），這樣稍微好一些。但即使這樣，現代讀者也仍然很可能把這「餅」理解成一種烘焙食物。為了避免這個問題，可譯為「一些乾無花果」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 直譯），「幾把乾無花果」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 直譯）。在很多時候，可以（並且最好）表達為「無花果壓成的團」或「乾無花果塊」。有些語言用專用詞語來指稱這種水果乾壓成的餅塊。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:12</a> ，可譯成「一塊無花果餅」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯），但「一些乾無花果」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）更好。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
